00:39:54.010 --> 00:39:58.690
someone who has experienced
a miracle, which

00:39:58.690 --> 00:39:59.890
I find quite surprising.

00:39:59.890 --> 00:40:03.760
Because if you are old,
then you have more time

00:40:03.760 --> 00:40:04.990
to experience a miracle.

00:40:04.990 --> 00:40:08.440
But actually younger people,
they believe in miracles

00:40:08.440 --> 00:40:11.977
more than the older people.

00:40:11.977 --> 00:40:13.810
And if you look at
newspapers and magazines,

00:40:13.810 --> 00:40:16.100
there are a lot of
examples of miracles,

00:40:16.100 --> 00:40:18.490
but often they are
just coincidences

00:40:18.490 --> 00:40:21.340
or some unexpected events.

00:40:21.340 --> 00:40:24.010
Even in sports, people
talk about miracles.

00:40:24.010 --> 00:40:28.420
And they are not miracles
in the religious sense.

00:40:28.420 --> 00:40:33.580
And these days, we don't really
see amazing religious miracles

00:40:33.580 --> 00:40:36.910
that are reported in the
religious scriptures.

00:40:36.910 --> 00:40:39.280
But maybe they are still
taking place somewhere,

00:40:39.280 --> 00:40:40.960
and we just don't
know about them.

00:40:44.884 --> 00:40:46.800
AUDIENCE: It's more of
an observation, really.

00:40:46.800 --> 00:40:49.091
I'll probably make more sense
after I've read the book.

00:40:49.091 --> 00:40:51.330
But I think we've almost
lost the vocabulary

00:40:51.330 --> 00:40:55.470
for looking into and expressing
anything that's a little bit

00:40:55.470 --> 00:41:00.030
strange, outside the remit of
faith or logic or whatever.

00:41:00.030 --> 00:41:03.360
If weird things happen to
you, it's probably best

00:41:03.360 --> 00:41:04.460
not to talk about them.

00:41:04.460 --> 00:41:07.860
And I think maybe we've kind
of lost that collectively.

00:41:07.860 --> 00:41:10.060
Virgin Mary on toast aside.

00:41:10.060 --> 00:41:12.195
So I'm looking forward
to reading this.

00:41:12.195 --> 00:41:16.860
YUJIN NAGASAWA:
So many people who

00:41:16.860 --> 00:41:19.470
have religious
experiences, they tend

00:41:19.470 --> 00:41:23.770
not to tell about it to anyone.

00:41:23.770 --> 00:41:29.130
They tend to be quite reserved
about their experiences, which

00:41:29.130 --> 00:41:30.420
is quite interesting.

00:41:30.420 --> 00:41:34.170
Because when you have a
strange experience, normally,

00:41:34.170 --> 00:41:36.700
you would want to tell someone.

00:41:36.700 --> 00:41:39.240
But when it comes to religious
or mystical experiences,

00:41:39.240 --> 00:41:43.020
they tend to keep them secret,
which is quite interesting.

00:41:43.020 --> 00:41:46.254
AUDIENCE: [INAUDIBLE].

00:41:46.254 --> 00:41:48.552
But in your case, it's
just a bit [INAUDIBLE],,

00:41:48.552 --> 00:41:49.677
it's a bit weird in person.

00:41:49.677 --> 00:41:54.090
It's kind of [INAUDIBLE]
right, I'm sure.

00:41:54.090 --> 00:41:56.690
YUJIN NAGASAWA: So do you
think that if you experience

00:41:56.690 --> 00:41:59.360
a miracle, you might think that
this is a little bit crazy.

00:41:59.360 --> 00:42:00.536
AUDIENCE: I wouldn't
experience a miracle,

00:42:00.536 --> 00:42:01.905
but I think that's probably
