00:43:29.760 --> 00:43:32.010
I didn't mean small children.

00:43:32.010 --> 00:43:35.070
I meant young adults.

00:43:35.070 --> 00:43:38.760
Obviously, if you ask
children, probably many of them

00:43:38.760 --> 00:43:41.880
believe in what
we call a miracle.

00:43:41.880 --> 00:43:45.930
Because according to some
cognitive scientists,

00:43:45.930 --> 00:43:49.330
children naturally
form religious beliefs.

00:43:49.330 --> 00:43:53.340
So they even say that if
you put a group of children

00:43:53.340 --> 00:43:56.160
on a remote island, they will
start their own religion.

00:43:56.160 --> 00:43:59.280
They form religious
beliefs naturally

00:43:59.280 --> 00:44:03.430
because there are some cognitive
and evolutionary reasons

00:44:03.430 --> 00:44:06.390
to form these beliefs.

00:44:06.390 --> 00:44:10.050
But the survey that I read
was about young adults.

00:44:10.050 --> 00:44:13.950
And then they seemed
to believe in miracles

00:44:13.950 --> 00:44:20.740
more than older people, which
I find quite puzzling, I think.

00:44:20.740 --> 00:44:23.490
But you could say that
young people, maybe they

00:44:23.490 --> 00:44:26.400
haven't had a lot of
experience in life,

00:44:26.400 --> 00:44:29.130
so maybe when they
encounter unusual events,

00:44:29.130 --> 00:44:33.030
they just attribute it to
something beyond nature.

00:44:40.230 --> 00:44:40.820
AUDIENCE: Hi.

00:44:40.820 --> 00:44:41.320
Thanks.

00:44:41.320 --> 00:44:43.570
So you talked about how
there's religious significance

00:44:43.570 --> 00:44:44.370
with a miracle.

00:44:44.370 --> 00:44:48.270
So I presume with
most known religions,

00:44:48.270 --> 00:44:51.410
there's some sort
of governing group

00:44:51.410 --> 00:44:55.250
that observe evidence,
or at least the stories

00:44:55.250 --> 00:44:59.490
behind miracles, and then
decides as a collective group

00:44:59.490 --> 00:45:01.530
whether that's a miracle or not.

00:45:01.530 --> 00:45:05.430
I presume that's a common
function of every religion,

00:45:05.430 --> 00:45:07.180
and I'd love to know if not.

00:45:07.180 --> 00:45:10.790
And are there sort of common
behaviors within these groups

00:45:10.790 --> 00:45:12.920
that observe the evidence
and decide whether they

00:45:12.920 --> 00:45:16.070
are miracles or not, are
there sometimes interesting

00:45:16.070 --> 00:45:19.210
divergence in approaches?

00:45:19.210 --> 00:45:23.040
YUJIN NAGASAWA: Yeah,
so obviously, miracles

00:45:23.040 --> 00:45:24.930
are very important
in Christianity

00:45:24.930 --> 00:45:28.710
because Jesus' birth was
miraculous and after his death,

00:45:28.710 --> 00:45:30.570
there was the
Resurrection, which

00:45:30.570 --> 00:45:32.910
is a very important
part of Christianity.

00:45:32.910 --> 00:45:35.020
And in the Catholic
tradition, there

00:45:35.020 --> 00:45:40.745
is a very rigorous process
of proving whether miracles

00:45:40.745 --> 00:45:42.750
have taken place.

00:45:42.750 --> 00:45:48.690
And that's important for
the process of canonization.

00:45:48.690 --> 00:45:52.830
So Mother Teresa was canonized
a couple of years ago.

00:45:52.830 --> 00:45:56.890
And that was based on
her posthumous miracles

00:45:56.890 --> 00:45:59.700
that allegedly she performed.

00:45:59.700 --> 00:46:04.150
So she cured a Brazilian
man who had brain tumors.

00:46:04.150 --> 00:46:08.370
And another person-- I
forgot what kind of condition

00:46:08.370 --> 00:46:13.020
she had-- but arguably,
she cured two people

00:46:13.020 --> 00:46:15.660
and healed two people.

00:46:15.660 --> 00:46:19.590
And on the basis of these
miracles, she was canonized.

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:21.990
So in the Catholic
tradition especially,

00:46:21.990 --> 00:46:24.490
miracles are very important.

00:46:24.490 --> 00:46:27.140
But my impression is that in
the Eastern tradition, Buddhism

00:46:27.140 --> 00:46:33.930
and Hinduism and so on,
miracles are not that important,

00:46:33.930 --> 00:46:37.091
at least not as important
as in Christianity.

00:46:41.420 --> 00:46:45.536
MODERATOR: Any more questions?

00:46:45.536 --> 00:46:46.660
Thank you very much, Yujin.

00:46:46.660 --> 00:46:47.290
That was very interesting.

00:46:47.290 --> 00:46:48.373
